\begin_layout Section
Conclusions and Limitations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:conclusions"

\end_inset

In conclusion, despite recent advances in the reach, speed, and afordability
 of Internet connectivity in sub-Saharan Africa, actual connectivity has
 been stagnant.
 This paper aims to see if this can in part be attributed to the dynamics
 of a two-sided market, such as Internet in a language, whereby the vicious
 circle of few users and little content perpetuates a situation of low levels
 of adoption.
 Due to the endogenous nature of two-sided markets, there are few methods
 of isolating a causal effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This paper exploits the introduction of the Setswana-language interface
 on 
\begin_inset Flex Code
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
google.co.za
\end_layout

\end_inset

, as a spillover of the development of this interface for 
\begin_inset Flex Code
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
google.co.bw
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and finds that it leads to a substantial increase in Internet usage and
 computer ownership among native Setswana speakers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This increase of Internet usage among the Setswana speaking population as
 a result of the newly introduced interface language on 
\begin_inset Flex Code
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
google.co.za
\end_layout

\end_inset

, suggests that there is a serious lack in the availability of local content
 in many African languages, which serves as an impediment to further Internet
 adoption here.
 Additionally, there was also an observably positive effect on computer
 ownership amongst adults.
 This suggests that the effect is unlikely to be ephemeral in nature, since
 computer ownership constitutes a more long-term investment in Internet
 access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally, the fact that this effect is not observed in cellphone ownership
 and expenditure, which is possibly a consequence of the fact that the interface
 cannot automatically switch and that the link `Setswana' is not directly
 visible from the landing page, suggests that it is important to make the
 link directly visible on the landing page in order to fully reach users.
\end_layout

